# {{PROJECT}} — working agreements for Claude

This repo runs the **Dark Software Factory**. The laws below are enforced by
hooks locally and re-enforced by CI as the authoritative boundary.

## Use the factory proactively

- If this repo is **not initialized yet** (no `.factory/config.json` — the
  SessionStart banner says so), run **`/factory-init`** before doing feature
  work, so the gates are armed rather than advisory.
- Prefer the factory's commands over ad-hoc git: **`/commit`** (drives the green
  gate), **`/review`** (adversarial panel → tech-debt), **`/roadmap`** (advance
  the plan). Treat the injected status line (next roadmap item, gate state, open
  tech-debt) as the source of truth for "where am I on the line."

## The laws

- **TDD is law.** Write the failing test first. `npm test` (typecheck →
  boundaries → unit → BDD → build → drift) is green at every commit. Never
  commit red.
- **Roadmap honesty.** Work `docs/ROADMAP.md` top-to-bottom. A checkbox flips to
  `[x]` only when its work merged with green tests.
- **Modules via public APIs only.** Cross-module access goes through a module's
  index; boundaries are CI-enforced.
- **Never release from red.** Releases are gated and smoke-tested on the ACTUAL
  built artifact.

## Code review → tech-debt

Any finding from a review — including adversarial reviews — that is **not fixed
in the current PR** must be opened as a GitHub issue labeled `tech-debt`, so it
doesn't get lost. Include: the location (`file:line`), what it is and why it
matters (a concrete failure or cost), its provenance (pre-existing vs. introduced),
and a suggested fix. Do not silently drop a finding or bury it in chat.
